## Database Management

### Migrations

```powershell
# Run all pending migrations (Supabase)
cd server
psql $env:DATABASE_URL -f migrations/001_initial_schema.sql

# Or use the Supabase CLI
supabase db push

# Or use the PowerShell script
.\run-migration-supabase.ps1
```

### Common Queries

```sql
-- Get all documents for a project (with Markdown content)
SELECT id, title, content, format, created_at
FROM documents
WHERE project_id = 'project-uuid'
AND format = 'markdown'
ORDER BY created_at DESC;

-- Get AI provider usage statistics
SELECT provider_name, COUNT(*) as usage_count, AVG(response_time) as avg_response_time
FROM ai_provider_usage
WHERE created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '7 days'
GROUP BY provider_name;

-- Get user's recent activity
SELECT al.action, al.resource_type, al.created_at, u.email
FROM audit_logs al
JOIN users u ON al.user_id = u.id
WHERE u.id = 'user-uuid'
ORDER BY al.created_at DESC
LIMIT 20;
```

### Backup & Restore

```powershell
# Backup Supabase database
pg_dump $env:DATABASE_URL > backup_$(Get-Date -Format 'yyyy-MM-dd').sql

# Using Supabase CLI
supabase db dump > backup_$(Get-Date -Format 'yyyy-MM-dd').sql

# Restore
psql $env:DATABASE_URL < backup_2024-10-20.sql

# Or use Supabase dashboard for point-in-time recovery (Pro plan)
```

